    "description": "<p>At 18th level your sense for danger reaches a&nbsp;preternatural level. Whenever you are forced to make&nbsp;a dexterity save against an area effect, you may use&nbsp;your reaction to move half your movement speed&nbsp;without provoking an attack of opportunity. If you&nbsp;end your movement outside of the affected area, you&nbsp;are unaffected. If you do not, you still have advantage&nbsp;on the save. Once you use this ability, you may not do&nbsp;so again until you finish a long rest unless you expend&nbsp;inspiration.</p>",
